Political Capital: Hungarian Guard increases government risk
According to the Risk Analysing Division of Political Capital, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, which was founded this August with the support of the "Movement for a Better Hungary", have increased the risk of Hungary and the region in several respects.
Among other things, the Institute's "Risk Warning Report" states that in connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk is the "intensification of the already existing ethnic tensions between the gypsies and the non-gypsy population in Hungary, which could even lead to violent ethnic conflicts in the short term".
The main reason for this is the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which presumably aims at provoking such a conflict, says the research institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure on the part of the political leaders: "People of public life have left the discussion of the Roma Left Question to representatives of radical political groupings who have now built their political strategy against the Roma Hungary".
It is believed that this would exacerbate the problem, make sensible dialogue impossible, favour limbs, and increase the likelihood of violent confrontations.
The research institute also believes that the activities of the Hungarian Guard, not least thanks to the enormous attention of the domestic and foreign media, "have seriously damaged Hungary's image abroad, particularly in terms of confidence in stability and democratic maturity."
We remember: since autumn 2006, the reorganisation of radical and extreme right-wing groups in Hungary has been continuously on the upswing, so that since summer 2007, several "national self-defense" organisations have been established.
"These groupings have in common that they define themselves as civil organizations, while they openly boast about preparing their members for - sometimes armed - defence tasks (civil protection, national defence, administrative protection), with reference to the incompetence of the police, the army, or the state itself", it was said.
And again, all this is done in accordance with the method that attempts to disguise various political aspirations as a bourgeois initiative based on the political and party oppression of the population.
The emphasis on the civil character and the form of the association thus do not merely serve to bypass legal obstacles that might arise in the course of the registration in court - it is also a political strategy.
As can be seen from the analysis, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are also a risk-enhancing factor for relations with neighbouring countries.
"In recent months, the Hungarian Guard has been cited as a potential source of danger in several neighbouring states, some ultranationalist politicians in certain neighbouring countries see the emergence of the Hungarian Guard as confirming its own anti-Hungarian policy.
All this has an impact on the political stability of the region "- it said.
From the point of view of the research institute, the establishment of the Hungarian Guard is not a single phenomenon in Central Eastern Europe, so the political risk for the entire region has increased.
As reported, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are comparable to those of the Bulgarian National Guard, which was founded in August 2007 by the far-right Bulgarian National Union (BNU).
In the background of the emergence of the Bulgarian Guard were the Roma mass expulsions that took place in a district of Sofia (Krasna Polyana).
