The White House leader stressed that the negotiations between Israel and the Palestinian authorities under Abbas are ultimately seeking a peace treaty to resolve all outstanding issues without exception, including key issues.
This designation comprises the three serious problems that are the main focus of the dispute between Israelis and Palestinians: the future borders of Palestine, the status of Jerusalem and the fate of the Arab refugees who were driven out of their homes in the present state of Israel in the course of the 1948 conflict.
After the American President, Abbas took the floor and insisted that the forthcoming negotiations should be conducted comprehensively and thoroughly, and that a settlement should be provided for all points, including Jerusalem, the refugees, the borders, the colonies, water and security.
When Olmert took the floor, he undertook to conduct the upcoming ceasefire negotiations directly and without interruption, and to make an effort to end them before the end of 2008.
Bush has set the deadline for implementing his vision of two states, one Palestinian and one Israeli, at the end of 2008.
Saudi Arabia has revealed that it has received Bush ’ s assurance in this sense before it decided to attend the conference.
