It is an honour for our company to work with a person who, no more and no less, has served as a role model for the current festival of the movement in America, Charlie Jones informed from C3 on Bilboard.com.
C3 hosts the Chicago Lollapalooza and Austin City Limits Music Festival.
Vineland, New Jersey, is a summer destination for camping holidays.
The festival will probably take place from August 8-10 on a 500 acre private farm about 40 minutes from Philadelphia.
The director of Festival Republic Melvin Benn, formerly known as Mean Fiddler, is one of the producers of the most prestigious festivals in the world.
In 1989 he took over the leadership of the Reading Festival in the United Kingdom, which attracts 80,000 people annually.
In 1999 Melvin Benn added the Leeds Festival to his portfolio, and then, in 2006, Festival Republic created the Latitude Festival in Henham Park in Suffolk.
Since 2002, Melvin Benn has also been working as a co-owner for the production, licensing concessions and organizational tasks of the Glastonbury Festival, which can now accommodate up to 177,500 people.
Charlie Jones of C3, who describes Glastonbury as the most inspiring event he has ever been to, says that his company and that of Melvin Benn are working side by side in order to offer the area a festival of European style.
We have chosen Philadelphia as a market and are working hard with the Fairmount Park Commission to create a festival in downtown Philadelphia, according to Charlie Jones.
We negotiated mt the city and the Commission was motivated and enthusiastic about this project.
Unfortunately, we have been stuck in political debates about the current administration, continues Charlie Jones.
"Fortunately we were able to discuss with Melvin Benn and we are preparing to create a great festival in an extraordinary place that will ultimately benefit the population."
C3 Presents brought the Lollapalooza Festival back to life in 2005 at the Grand Park Chicago, after having made its mark in 2002 with the Austin City Limits Music Festival in the world of the festival.
The two events were able to generate $9.8 million and $11.8 million in gross tax transactions in 2007.
These two festivals take place in an urban environment.
"The European model of Melvin Benn is a rural festival, whereas ours are more likely to take place on the urban green areas," says Charlie Jones.
"The aim is to merge these two concepts in one way or another in order to simultaneously give the impression of a rural festival in the European and an urban way in the American way."
Vineland is about half way between Philadelphia and Atlantic City.
"The community of Vineland, including the mayor, takes on the burden of this event with joy," says Charlie Jones.
The latter refuses to disclose the terms of the agreement, but he confirms "that they are sufficiently interesting to invest in such an event and to record a festival that will hopefully have a long life."
Charlie Jones says that the recording capacity of the festival is "very large", corresponding to about 80,000 people at the Bonnaroo Music Festival in Tennessee.
He says that the invitations have been sent to the groups, but that nothing could be confirmed when they were printed.
"Vineland will offer tasteful rock, but the music will be very diverse, hoping to attract all kinds of spectators," says Charlie Jones.
His partners of C3, who received the Top Independent promoter ’ s award of the last Bollboard Touring Awards, are Charlie Walker and Charles Attal.
