Popular will have its 200 credit institutions open 12 hours a day from Monday to Friday.
Popular has decided to modernize a large part of its stores.
A total of 200 of them are located in the strongest regions of Spain.
For the institute, which operates under the brand name Popular Max, these branches represent a major milestone.
But also for the remaining Spanish institutes, since Popular is the first banking group dares to extend the opening hours of its branches weekdays to 20.30h and to start on Saturdays from 10h to 20.30h.
The banking group BBVA, which also repeatedly announced the extension of its opening hours in the branches, has not yet taken a definitive decision.
The Bank ’ s current negotiations with the trade unions seem to aim for an agreement in which 75% of all branches are closed on Saturdays and open in the afternoon on a weekday, albeit not for the customers.
Whether other banks join the new initiative that adapts to business opening times will depend on Popular Bank ’ s experience.
And it is precisely this that Popular intends to pursue with her project.
The aim is to extend the opening times of those branches which, due to their location, can capture the merchandise of independent, small and medium-sized companies, but also those of large department stores.
The Bank intends to open the new 200 branches over the next 18 months, as these are not new but changed opening hours.
For this purpose, the bank will redesign the premises of those branches that are already located in business zones and at the same time align them with the individual customer profile of the different zones.
The extension of the opening hours is connected with a new interior design of the branches, which is characterized by a more up-to-date, colorful design.
