The Congress agrees to the MIFID Directive, which entered into force on 1 November.
Parallel to the parliamentary drafting, which ended its meeting today with the Senate Congress resolution on the supplementary / amendments to the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law with the intention of enabling the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the Congressmen and Senate Members, who had pursued the goal in their negotiations and votes to establish the best possible regulation, which guarantees the security of investors and regulates the individual entrepreneurs' activities in order to guarantee a generally efficient market event.
In addition to modernising the financial markets, MIFID, which redefines the Securities Services Regulation, is pursuing an improvement in investor protection, increasing the control claim of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and promoting cooperation between the various control authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive makes it possible to offer financial advice to both specialised companies and to individuals or legal entities, and also contributes to the establishment of new financial services companies (ESIS), the consulting firms associated with the investment and mediation companies of securities.
It also expands the number of systems for implementing financial transactions, adding to regulated circulation markets the multilateral systems of securities business and the systems for internationalising trade contracts, which would eventually compete with current economic operators.
The law obliges investment companies to identify the focal points of their business profile, the confrontation and the forms of dealing with risks on the market and to register all projects carried out in order to facilitate their control role for CNMV.
In retrospect, the Congress ’ s Economic Commission envisaged further changes, with the US mortgage and banking crisis confirming the decision that, due to its high risk level for the investor, the bond provided with titles must now be regarded as complex financial resources.
Furthermore, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal restriction of the fields of work of diploma economists was used; 30 years after 1977, the Regulation limiting the areas of work reserved for economists was adopted.
For its part, the Senate established new positions in the financial sector, such as that of the business mediator, who works on external account, does not require authorization from the CNMV and can offer its services for the commercialization of products and for customer acquisition simultaneously several investment companies.
The harmonised consumer price index (CPI) rose by five tenths in November and now stands at 4.1%.
The indicator used by Eurostat to assess the inflation rate within the European Union delivers the average price trend in Spain in November.
Its publication complies with the principles of Eurostat and the European Central Bank (ECB), which aim to achieve a local and quality comparison with US products through the disclosure of the data.
