Which insurance is best for me?
The car insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which depends again on different factors, e.g. on age, gender, time of the production of the driving licence, marital status, type of the car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
It is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
Firstly, we need to be clear about what we have to do here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insured party.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to submit the corresponding compensation sum in the event of a damage.
The insurance premium is the price of insurance, which consists of several factors, including age, gender, time of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices in accordance with the statistics, so that higher contributions are due in the event of a higher risk of accidents.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women will have to pay less, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same also applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the enterprises, these tend to fewer accidents like single persons.
The benefits attached to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly to select exactly the car insurance that best suits his personal needs.
At this point, we are now listing the most important points that should be taken into account when selecting an insurance policy in order to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
Those under 25 years of age encounter numerous obstacles when choosing low-cost insurance, such as the low driving practice and the young driving licence.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out comprehensive insurance, there are nevertheless cheaper alternatives.
The careful drivers can select a full debt with excess, so that the benefits of a full debt insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract means that the customer has to pay part of the amount caused by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the contract is concluded and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the amount to be paid, says Luis Noguera, Spain ’ s main representative at First Europa, an online insurance mediation company.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused by his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here is a Council.
If you are under 25 years old, it is in your hand to lower insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction of the basic tariff at the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in these tariffs.
The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its proceeds.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can afford to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25 year mark is exceeded, it is easier for the drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
It is therefore most sensible to opt for a comprehensive insurance with excess.
Usually, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, and adds that most of the accidents occur in the second year of practice after the beginner ’ s fear has been lifted.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer, who does not have children, to take out a comprehensive insurance; of course only if the financial situation of the respective person allows it.
The insurers consider married couples with children to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly their contributions are low.
In this case, full insurance with deductible (for an amount of 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which will only be used for the third vehicle year.
They are generally more relaxed and have a greater purchasing power, which allows them to make a higher contribution payment, says Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a comprehensive insurance with deductible (for an amount of 150 Euros), or an extended insurance, which only uses with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accident damage, but also because it involves high costs, which require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
