The Venus was perhaps once a pleasant place to live, scientists said yesterday.
Data from a European spacecraft on an orbit show that the planet is even more like a deviated twin of the Earth than was previously known.
Venus is the nearest planetary neighbour of the Earth.
The two worlds are about the same size and have similar planetary orbits, but Venus is a little closer to the Sun.
Billions of years ago, Venus would have ruled conditions that would have been very similar to those on Earth and could even have been habitable, scientists believe today.
